nodes.bodyText:
The reason to drop the polling outside here is that we already specifically do polling inside doStop() and doStart() as below. The polling will take 1000 seconds total. In the case of a hang blocking call, we will wait twice as much long. It is not necessary to poll and then immediately poll again. I added unit test and also did integration testing with AWS.
doStop(...) { 
	stop(...) {
		setCloudVmInstanceStatuses(...){
			pollerUtil.waitFor(...);
		}
	}
}

